                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Storer</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 26.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Mr. Rives’s No. 19, of the 18th ultimo, has been
                    received.</p>
                <p>The recognition accorded by the Austro-Hungarian Government to John Steel Twells
                    as “commercial (consular) agent” of the United States at Carlsbad is regarded by
                    the Department as sufficient.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
